INSTALLING GOOGLE CLOUD CLI 

  

Follow this link(https://cloud.google.com/sdk/docs/install) and find the tar.gz package that needs to be downloaded in the step 2 of that documentation. 

  

After downloading the required package, extract it to any location on your file system. The extracted folder will be named as “google-cloud-sdk”. 

  

Open an instance of the terminal on that location where the sdk folder exists and run the following command:  

./google-cloud-sdk/install.sh  

  

After doing this follow this link for further cloud cli setup steps: https://k8s.optum.com/documentation/management_tools/kubectl_cli/#kubectl-cloud-native-id-configuration 

  

