Now that the HCC K8S team migrated our stage namespaces to the nonprod cluster ctcnonprdusr001, I have updated the CICD for the new namespaces. I have also shutdown the pods in the old namespaces.  

  

Here are the details to access the new namespaces on your local machines and in Lens. The documentation is linked below for more details if needed.  

https://k8s.optum.com/documentation/getting-started/ 

  

Login to https://myworkaccount.microsoft.com/ using your cloud native id (i.e. jwang49@optumcloud.com) in your default browser 
In your terminal: 
cd $HOME/Library/Preferences/google/anthos/ 
Copy this file to the above location: 
i.      https://k8s.optum.com/documentation/kubectl-anthos-config.yaml 

If you already have a file kubectl-anthos-config.yaml, you will need to delete it and copy the latest version from the above link 
Login to google cloud in your terminal using your cloud native id (i.e. jwang49@optumcloud.com) : 
gcloud anthos auth login --cluster ctcnonprdusr001 
Run this command: 
kubectl config use-context <cluster_name>-<cloud_native_id> 
i.e. kubectl config use-context ctcnonprdusr001-jwang49@optumcloud.com 
Switch to the new namespace: 
hcpctl login 
For PRUN stage: 
                        i.   curl -sSL https://github.optum.com/raw/rjury/hcck8s_prm_demo/master/setup-kubeconfig.sh | bash -s -- fds-paperless/naas-v1/ctcnonprdusr001-provider-paperless-stage 

                       ii.   kubectl config use-context ctcnonprdusr001_provider-paperless-stage_provider-paperless-stage-hcc-naas-admin 

For PEN stage: 
                        i.   curl -sSL https://github.optum.com/raw/rjury/hcck8s_prm_demo/master/setup-kubeconfig.sh | bash -s -- fds-paperless/naas-v1/ctcnonprdusr001-provider-email-notifications-stage-ctc 

                       ii.   kubectl config use-context ctcnonprdusr001_provider-email-notifications-stage-ctc_provider-email-notifications-stage-ctc-hcc-naas-admin 

 

 

 

 

 

